
  <sn><md>### The Basic Elements of the State {.text-center}

If we analyse the concept of state, we will notice four essential elements of it: the people, the specific geographical territory, the government, and the sovereignty. Each state consists of these four elements.

```bash
THE STATE
│
├── People
│   ├── Politically organized citizens
│   ├── No fixed number required
│   └── Foundation of the state
│
├── Specific Geographical Territory
│   ├── Land, sea, and air space
│   ├── Defined borders
│   ├── Can be large or small
│   └── Basis of national identity &amp; security
│
├── Government
│   ├── Law-making branch
│   ├── Executive (administration)
│   ├── Judiciary
│   └── Controls and manages the state
│
└── Sovereignty
    ├── Supreme and absolute power
    ├── Internal authority over citizens
    ├── External independence from other states
    └── Essential for state recognition
```
</md></sn>
